  5 var GenericStar = {};
  6 
  7 /**
  8  * Creates a new Core for Generic Star. The core handles holding instances of all other
  9  * useful Generic Star objects.
 10  * @param {Node} domGraphics the DOM Canvas object that we will be drawing to
 11  * @param {Boolean} usePhysics whether or not to use the Box2D Physics Engine
 12  * @param {Object} gravity an object containing x and y, which represent x and y
 13  * 			components of the generic gravity force. Can be null for no gravity.
 14  */
 15 GenericStar.Core = function(domGraphics, usePhysics, gravity) {
 16 	var useGrav = true;
 17 	if (gravity === null) {
 18 		gravity = {x: 0, y: 0};
 19 		useGrav = false;
 20 	}
 21 	this.DEBUG = true;
 22 	this.input = new GenericStar.Input();
 23 	this.input.attachMouseListener(domGraphics);
 24 	this.sound = new GenericStar.Sound();
 25 	if (usePhysics) this.physics = new GenericStar.Physics.Controller(this, gravity);
 26 	this.graphics = null;
 27 	
 28 	this.start = function(stepCallback) {
 29 		this.graphics = new GenericStar.Graphics(this, domGraphics, stepCallback);
 30 	};
 31 	
 32 	/**
 33 	 * Gets whether or not we are using gravity in this game.
 34 	 * @returns {Boolean} true if we are using gravity.
 35 	 */
 36 	this.isUsingGravity = function() {
 37 		return useGrav;
 38 	};
 39 };

 41 /**
 42  * Creates a Graphics Handler. Only the core should create these.
 43  * @class Handles drawing to the canvas.
 44  * @param {GenericStar.Core} core the core object
 45  * @param {Canvas} canvas the canvas we are drawing to
 46  * @param {Function} drawCallback {(GenericStar.Graphics):()} 
 47  * 			A function that gets called at the draw stage of each frame
 48  */
 49 GenericStar.Graphics = function(core, canvas, drawCallback) {
 50 	var GfxPlugins = {WebGL: {}, Canvas: {}};
 51 	
 52 	GfxPlugins.WebGL.init = false;
 53 	
 54 	var canvasSize = {
 55 		w: 640,
 56 		h: 480
 57 	};
 58 	
 59 	/**
 60 	 * Creates a WebGL Plugin.
 61 	 * @class This plugin handles drawing in an OpenGL context.
 62 	 * @param {Canvas} canvas the canvas to draw to
 63 	 * @param {GenericStar.Graphics} gfx the Graphics object that spawned this (contains global settings)
 64 	 * @param {Function} drawCallback {(GfxPlugins.WebGL):()} this function is called every frame
 65 	 * 						in the main draw loop
 66 	 */
 67 	GfxPlugins.WebGL = function(canvas, gfx, drawCallback) {
 68 		//PRIVATE VARIABLES
 69 		var gl;
 70 		var shaderProgram;
 71 		var lastTime = 0;
 72 		
 73 		var vertexPositionBuffer;
 74 		var vertexTextureCoordBuffer;
 75 		var thisPlugin = this;
 76 		
 77 		var canvasWidth = 1;
 78 		var canvasHeight= 1;
 79 		
 80 		//PRIVATE FUNCTIONS-----------------------------------
 81 		//SHADER FUNCTIONS
 82 		/**
 83 		 * Loads a shader from source code. If failure, can print to debug log.
 84 		 * @param type of shader (gl.GL_VERTEX_SHADER or gl.GL_FRAGMENT_SHADER)
 85 		 * @param {String} shaderSrc source code to load as a shader
 86 		 * @returns {Shader} the shader object created by GL
 87 		 */
 88 		function loadShader(type, shaderSrc) {
 89 			var shader = gl.createShader(type);
 90 			if (shader == 0) return 0;
 91 			gl.shaderSource(shader, shaderSrc);
 92 			gl.compileShader(shader);
 93 			var compiled = gl.getShaderParameter(shader, gl.COMPILE_STATUS);
 94 
 95 			if (!compiled && core.DEBUG) {
 96 				console.error("COULD NOT COMPILE SHADER: ["+gl.getShaderInfoLog(shader)+"]");
 97 				gl.deleteShader(shader);
 98 				return 0;
 99 			}
100 			return shader;
101 		}
102 
103 		/**
104 		 * Loads a program consisting of a vertex and fragment shader into the GL context.
105 		 * @param {Shader} vertShaderSrc the vertex shader
106 		 * @param {Shader} fragShaderSrc the fragment shader
107 		 */
108 		function loadGlProgram(vertShaderSrc, fragShaderSrc) {
109 			var programObject;
110 			var linked;
111 
112 			// Load the vertex/fragment shaders
113 			var vertexShader = loadShader(gl.VERTEX_SHADER, vertShaderSrc);
114 			if (vertexShader == 0) return 0;
115 			var fragmentShader = loadShader(gl.FRAGMENT_SHADER, fragShaderSrc);
116 			if (fragmentShader == 0) {
117 				gl.deleteShader(vertexShader);
118 				return 0;
119 			}
120 
121 			// Create the program object
122 			programObject = gl.createProgram();
123 			if (programObject == 0) return 0;
124 			gl.attachShader(programObject, vertexShader);
125 			gl.attachShader(programObject, fragmentShader);
126 			gl.linkProgram(programObject);
127 			linked = gl.getProgramParameter(programObject, gl.LINK_STATUS);
128 
129 			if (!linked && core.DEBUG) {
130 				console.error("COULD NOT LINK GL PROGRAM: ["+gl.getProgramInfoLog(programObject)+"]");
131 				gl.deleteProgram(programObject);
132 				return 0;
133 			}
134 			gl.deleteShader(vertexShader);
135 			gl.deleteShader(fragmentShader);
136 			return programObject;
137 		}
138 		
139 	    //CONSTRUCTOR CODE========================================
140 		if (!GfxPlugins.WebGL.init) {
141 			//TODO: init html stuff here with html dom injection
142 			GfxPlugins.WebGL.init = true;
143 		}
144 		
145 		//Init GL
146 		try {
147 	        gl = canvas.getContext("experimental-webgl");
148 	        gl.viewportWidth = canvas.width;
149 	        gl.viewportHeight = canvas.height;
150 	    } catch (e) {}
151 	    if (!gl && core.DEBUG) {
152 	        console.error("FATAL ERROR: Could not initialise WebGL.");
153 	    }
154 	    
155 	    var shaderProgram = loadGlProgram(
156 	    	//VERTEX SHADER
157 	       "attribute vec3 aVertexPosition;	\n\
158 	    	attribute vec2 aTextureCoord;	\n\
159 	    	uniform mat4 uMVMatrix;			\n\
160 	    	uniform mat4 uPMatrix;			\n\
161 	    	varying vec2 vTextureCoord;		\n\
162 	    	void main(void) {				\n\
163 	    		gl_Position = uPMatrix * uMVMatrix * vec4(aVertexPosition, 1.0);	\n\
164 	    		vTextureCoord = aTextureCoord;	\n\
165 	    	}",
166 	    
167 	    	//FRAGMENT SHADER
168 		   "#ifdef GL_ES 				\n\
169 		 		precision highp float; 	\n\
170 			#endif						\n\
171 			varying vec2 vTextureCoord;	\n\
172 			uniform sampler2D uSampler; \n\
173 			void main(void) {			\n\
174 				gl_FragColor = texture2D(uSampler, vec2(vTextureCoord.s, vTextureCoord.t));		\n\
175 			}"
176 	    );
177 
178         gl.useProgram(shaderProgram);
179         shaderProgram.vertexPositionAttribute = gl.getAttribLocation(shaderProgram, "aVertexPosition");
180         shaderProgram.textureCoordAttribute   = gl.getAttribLocation(shaderProgram, "aTextureCoord");
181         gl.enableVertexAttribArray(shaderProgram.vertexPositionAttribute);
182         gl.enableVertexAttribArray(shaderProgram.textureCoordAttribute);
183         shaderProgram.pMatrixUniform  = gl.getUniformLocation(shaderProgram, "uPMatrix");
184         shaderProgram.mvMatrixUniform = gl.getUniformLocation(shaderProgram, "uMVMatrix");
185         shaderProgram.samplerUniform  = gl.getUniformLocation(shaderProgram, "uSampler");
186 	    gl.clearColor(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0);
187 	    gl.disable(gl.GL_DEPTH_TEST);
188         gl.enable(gl.BLEND);
189         gl.blendFunc(gl.SRC_ALPHA, gl.ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA);
190 	    
191 	    //Init transform matrices
192 	    var mvMatrix = mat4.create();
193 	    var mvMatrixStack = [];
194 	    var pMatrix = mat4.create();
195 	    
196 	    //Init Buffers
197 	    var cubeVertexTextureCoordBuffer = gl.createBuffer();
198 	    var cubeVertexPositionBuffer = gl.createBuffer();
199 	    var linePosBuffer = gl.createBuffer();
200 	    var lineColBuffer = gl.createBuffer();
201 	    
202 	    
203 	    //PRIVATE METHODS---------------------------------
204 	    var degToRad = function(degrees) {
205 	        return degrees * Math.PI / 180;
206 	    };
207 
208 	    var drawframe = function() {
209 	        requestAnimFrame(drawframe);
210 	        
211 	        canvasWidth = gfx.getCanvasWidth();
212 	        canvasHeight = gfx.getCanvasHeight();
213 	        //console.log(gl.viewportWidth+", "+gl.viewportHeight);
214 	        //gl.viewport(0, 0, gl.viewportWidth, gl.viewportHeight);
215 	        gl.viewport(0, 0, canvasWidth, canvasHeight);
216 	        gl.clear(gl.COLOR_BUFFER_BIT | gl.DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT);
217 	        gl.hint(gl.GL_PERSPECTIVE_CORRECTION_HINT,gl.GL_NICEST);
218 	        mat4.ortho(0, canvasWidth, canvasHeight, 0, 0, 1, pMatrix);
219 	        
220 	        drawCallback(thisPlugin);
221 	        
222 	        //calculate fps
223 	        var timeNow = new Date().getTime();
224 	        if (lastTime != 0) {
225 	            var elapsed = timeNow - lastTime;
226 	        }
227 	        lastTime = timeNow;
228 	    };
229 	    
230 	    //PUBLIC METHODS-----------------------------------
231 	    /**
232 	     * This function loads an image into OpenGL Memory. Note that if you are using
233 	     * the scaffolding, this is all taken care of by the Sprite Handler, and you should
234 	     * probably be using <code>getImage</code> to get sprites for drawing.
235 	     * @param {String} img the filename of the image to load in
236 	     * @param {Function} callback {(GfxPlugins.WebGL.Texture):()} this function is called upon completion of loading
237 	     * @param {Boolean} [tile] true if you plan on tiling this image. 
238 	     * 			If true, the image must have width and height values that are powers of two.
239 	     */
240 	    this.loadImage = function(img, callback, tile) {
241 	    	if (tile == undefined) tile = false;
242 	    	var texRet = new GfxPlugins.WebGL.Texture(gl.createTexture(), new Image(), tile);
243 	    	texRet.image.onload = function () {
244 	    		gl.bindTexture(gl.TEXTURE_2D, texRet.texture);
245 	    		gl.pixelStorei(gl.UNPACK_FLIP_Y_WEBGL, true);
246 	    	    gl.texImage2D(gl.TEXTURE_2D, 0, gl.RGBA, gl.RGBA, gl.UNSIGNED_BYTE, texRet.image);
247 	    	    gl.texParameteri(gl.TEXTURE_2D, gl.TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER, gl.LINEAR);
248 	    	    gl.texParameteri(gl.TEXTURE_2D, gl.TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER, gl.LINEAR_MIPMAP_LINEAR);
249 	    	    if (!texRet.tile) {
250 	    	    	gl.texParameteri(gl.TEXTURE_2D, gl.TEXTURE_WRAP_S, gl.CLAMP_TO_EDGE); //fix power of 2
251 		    	    gl.texParameteri(gl.TEXTURE_2D, gl.TEXTURE_WRAP_T, gl.CLAMP_TO_EDGE); //fix power of 2
252 	    	    } else {
253 	    	    	gl.texParameteri(gl.TEXTURE_2D, gl.TEXTURE_WRAP_S, gl.REPEAT); //fix power of 2
254 		    	    gl.texParameteri(gl.TEXTURE_2D, gl.TEXTURE_WRAP_T, gl.REPEAT); //fix power of 2
255 	    	    }
256 	    	    gl.generateMipmap(gl.TEXTURE_2D);
257 	    	    gl.bindTexture(gl.TEXTURE_2D, null);
258 	    	 
259 	    	    var maxSize = gl.getParameter(gl.MAX_TEXTURE_SIZE);
260 	    	    if (core.DEBUG && (texRet.image.width > maxSize || texRet.image.height > maxSize)) {
261 	    		    console.error("ERROR: Your hardware cannot load textures of this size.");
262 	    	    }
263 	    	    
264 	    	    callback(texRet);
265 	        };
266 
267 	        texRet.image.src = img;
268 	    };
269 	    
270 	    
271 	    /**
272 	     * Draws a given texture tiled to a given dimension.
273 	     * @param {GfxPlugins.WebGL.Texture} tex the texture to draw. Note - it must be enabled to tile when you loaded it.
274 	     * @param {Number} x the x position (in pixels) to draw at
275 	     * @param {Number} y the y position (in pixels) to draw at
276 	     * @param {Number} w the width in pixels of the image
277 	     * @param {Number} h the height in pixels of the image
278 	     * @param {Number} [rot=0] the rotation of the image once drawn (in degrees).
279 	     * @param {Number} [cx=0] the center of the image to rotate about.
280 	     * @param {Number} [cy=0] the center of the image to rotate about.
281 	     * @param {Number} [rx=1] the number of times to tile this image horizontally
282 	     * @param {Number} [ry=1] the number of times to tile this image vertically
283 	     */
284 	    this.drawSpriteTiled = function(tex, x, y, w, h, rot, cx, cy, rx, ry) {
285 	    	if (core.DEBUG && !tex.tile) console.error("Error: cannot tile this image ["+tex.image.src+"]");
286 	    	var imgw = parseInt(tex.image.width);
287 	    	var imgh = parseInt(tex.image.height);
288 	    	if (rx == undefined) rx = 1;
289 	    	if (ry == undefined) ry = 1;
290 	    	if (rx <= 0) rx = 1;
291 	    	if (ry <= 0) ry = 1;
292 	    	this.drawSprite(tex, x, y, w, h, rot, cx, cy, 0, 0, 1/rx, 1/ry);
293 	    };
294 	    
295 	    /**
296 	     * Draws a given texture tiled to a given dimension.
297 	     * @param {GfxPlugins.WebGL.Texture} tex the texture to draw. Note - it must be enabled to tile when you loaded it.
298 	     * @param {Number} x the x position (in pixels) to draw at
299 	     * @param {Number} y the y position (in pixels) to draw at
300 	     * @param {Number} [w] the width in pixels of the image
301 	     * @param {Number} [h] the height in pixels of the image
302 	     * @param {Number} [rot=0] the rotation of the image once drawn (in degrees).
303 	     * @param {Number} [cx=0] the center of the image to rotate about.
304 	     * @param {Number} [cy=0] the center of the image to rotate about.
305 	     * @param {Number} [fx=0] the x frame index to use if this is a sprite-sheet
306 	     * @param {Number} [fy=0] the y frame index to use if this is a sprite-sheet
307 	     * @param {Number} [fw=1] how many columns of sprites there are in this sprite-sheet
308 	     * @param {Number} [fh=1] how many rows of sprites there are in this sprite-sheet
309 	     */
310 	    this.drawSprite = function(tex, x, y, w, h, rot, cx, cy, fx, fy, fw, fh) {
311 	    	if (x == undefined) x = 0;
312 	    	if (y == undefined) y = 0;
313 	    	if (rot == undefined) rot = 0;
314 	    	if (cx == undefined) cx = 0;
315 	    	if (cy == undefined) cy = 0;
316 	    	if (fx == undefined) fx = 0;
317 	    	if (fy == undefined) fy = 0;
318 	    	if (fw == undefined) fw = 1;
319 	    	if (fh == undefined) fh = 1;
320 	    	fx /= fw;
321 	    	fy /= fh;
322 	    	fw = 1 / fw;
323 	    	fh = 1 / fh;
324 	    	if (w == undefined) w = parseInt(tex.image.width) * fw;
325 	    	if (h == undefined) h = parseInt(tex.image.height)* fh;
326 	    	
327 	    	rot = -rot * Math.PI / 180;
328 	    	cx *= -1;
329 	    	cy *= -1;
330 	    	
331 	    	var vertices = [
332 	              cx, cy+h,  0.0,
333 	              cx+w, cy+h,  0.0,
334 	              cx+w, cy,  0.0,
335 	              cx, cy,  0.0 ];
336 	    	
337     		var cells = (vertices.length / 3)*2;
338 	    	var cellRepeat = [fx, fy, fx+fw, fy, fx+fw, fy+fh, fx, fy+fh];
339 	    	texCoords = [];
340 	    	for(var i=0; i < cells; i++) {
341 	    		texCoords[i] = cellRepeat[i % cellRepeat.length];
342 	    	}
343 	    	
344 	    	if (texCoords.length % 8 != 0 && core.DEBUG) console.warn("DrawSprite Warning: texcoords error: ["+texCoords+"]");
345 	    	
346 	    	mat4.identity(mvMatrix);
347 	        mat4.translate(mvMatrix, [x, y, 0.0]);
348 	        mat4.rotateZ(mvMatrix, rot);
349 	    	this.draw3D(vertices, texCoords, tex);
350 	    };
351 	    
352 	    /**
353 	     * Draws a 3D Texture to the WebGL Canvas. Only use if you know what you're doing.
354 	     * @param {Number[]} vertcoord the vertex coordinates to use in drawing
355 	     * @param {Number[]} texcoord the texture coordinates to use in drawing
356 	     * @param {GfxPlugins.WebGL.Texture} texture the texture to draw
357 	     */
358 	    this.draw3D = function(vertcoord, texcoord, texture) {
359 	    	gl.bindBuffer(gl.ARRAY_BUFFER, cubeVertexPositionBuffer);
360 	    	gl.bufferData(gl.ARRAY_BUFFER, new Float32Array(vertcoord), gl.STATIC_DRAW);
361 	        cubeVertexPositionBuffer.itemSize = 3;
362 	        cubeVertexPositionBuffer.numItems = vertcoord.length / 3;
363 	        gl.bindBuffer(gl.ARRAY_BUFFER, cubeVertexPositionBuffer);
364 	        gl.vertexAttribPointer(shaderProgram.vertexPositionAttribute, cubeVertexPositionBuffer.itemSize, gl.FLOAT, false, 0, 0);
365 	        
366 		    gl.bindBuffer(gl.ARRAY_BUFFER, cubeVertexTextureCoordBuffer);
367 	        gl.bufferData(gl.ARRAY_BUFFER, new Float32Array(texcoord), gl.STATIC_DRAW);
368 	        cubeVertexTextureCoordBuffer.itemSize = 2;
369 	        cubeVertexTextureCoordBuffer.numItems = texcoord.length / 2;
370 	        gl.bindBuffer(gl.ARRAY_BUFFER, cubeVertexTextureCoordBuffer);
371 	        gl.vertexAttribPointer(shaderProgram.textureCoordAttribute, cubeVertexTextureCoordBuffer.itemSize, gl.FLOAT, false, 0, 0);
372 	    	
373 	    	gl.activeTexture(gl.TEXTURE0);
374 	        gl.bindTexture(gl.TEXTURE_2D, texture.texture);
375 	        gl.uniform1i(shaderProgram.samplerUniform, 0);
376 	        gl.texParameteri ( gl.TEXTURE_2D, gl.TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER, gl.NEAREST );
377 	        gl.uniformMatrix4fv(shaderProgram.pMatrixUniform, false, pMatrix);
378 	        gl.uniformMatrix4fv(shaderProgram.mvMatrixUniform, false, mvMatrix);
379 	        gl.drawArrays(gl.TRIANGLE_FAN, 0, cubeVertexPositionBuffer.numItems);
380 	    };
381 	    
382 	    drawframe();
383 	};
384 	
385 	/**
386 	 * Creates a new Texture object. Used internally; simply
387 	 * pass it into WebGL methods, don't try to use it or modify its
388 	 * parameters manually.
389 	 * @class Represents a texture that can be drawn in WebGL
390 	 * @param {GLTexture} tex the texture
391 	 * @param {Image} image the DOM Image this texture was loaded from
392 	 * @param {Boolean} tile whether or not this texture supports tiling
393 	 */
394 	GfxPlugins.WebGL.Texture = function(tex, image, tile) {
395 		this.texture = tex;
396 		this.image = image;
397 		this.tile = tile;
398 	};
399 	
400 	/**
401 	 * Sets the size of the canvas we're plugged into.
402 	 * @param {Number} w the new width of the canvas
403 	 * @param {Number} h the new height of the canvas
404 	 */
405 	this.setCanvasSize = function(w, h) {
406 		w = (w <= 0) ? 1 : w;
407 		h = (h <= 0) ? 1 : h;
408 		canvasSize.w = w;
409 		canvasSize.h = h;
410 	};
411 	
412 	/**
413 	 * Gets the width of the canvas
414 	 * @returns {Number} the width of the canvas
415 	 */
416 	this.getCanvasWidth = function() {
417 		return canvasSize.w;
418 	};
419 	
420 	/**
421 	 * Gets the height of the canvas
422 	 * @returns {Number} the height of the canvas
423 	 */
424 	this.getCanvasHeight = function() {
425 		return canvasSize.h;
426 	};
427 	
428 	/**
429 	 * Gets the plugin that is currently being used.
430 	 * @returns {GfxPlugins.WebGL} the web gl plugin
431 	 */
432 	this.getPlugin = function() {
433 		return gfxPlugin;
434 	};
435 	
436 	//final init code
437 	var gfxPlugin = new GfxPlugins.WebGL(canvas, this, drawCallback);
438 };

440 /**
441  * Creates an Input Handler.
442  * @class This class handles listening for keyboard / mouse input.
443  */
444 GenericStar.Input = function() {
445 	var keyState = new Array();
446 	var btnState = new Array();
447 	
448 	var attached = false;
449 	var mousePos = {x: 0, y: 0};
450 	var mouseState = new Array();
451 	var mouseBtn = new Array();
452 	
453 	window.onkeydown = function(e) {
454 		keyState[e.keyCode] = true;
455 		btnState[e.keyCode] = true;
456 	};
457 	
458 	window.onkeyup = function(e) {
459 		keyState[e.keyCode] = false;
460 		btnState[e.keyCode] = false;
461 	};
462 	
463 	/**
464 	 * Gets whether or not a key is being pressed.
465 	 * @param {Number} key the key to check. For possible keys, see GenericStar.Input.Key.
466 	 * @returns {Boolean} true if the key is being pressed
467 	 */
468 	this.isKeyDown = function(key) {
469 		btnState[key] = false;
470 		return keyState[key];
471 	};
472 	
473 	/**
474 	 * Gets whether or not a key has just been tapped.
475 	 * @param {Number} key the key to check. For possible keys, see GenericStar.Input.Key.
476 	 * @returns {Boolean} true if the key has just been pressed and is not being held.
477 	 */
478 	this.isKeyDownBtn = function(key) {
479 		var ret = btnState[key];
480 		btnState[key] = false;
481 		return ret;
482 	};
483 	
484 	/**
485 	 * Gets whether or not a mouse button is down.
486 	 * @param {Number} mouse the button to check against. For a list of buttons, see GenericStar.Input.Mouse.
487 	 * @returns {Boolean} true if pressed, false otherwise.
488 	 */
489 	this.isMouseDown = function(mouse) {
490 		mouseBtn[mouse] = false;
491 		return mouseState[mouse];
492 	};
493 	
494 	/**
495 	 * Gets whether or not a mouse button was just pressed.
496 	 * @param {Number} mouse the button to check against. For a list of buttons, see GenericStar.Input.Mouse.
497 	 * @returns {Boolean} true if pressed just pressed and not if being held.
498 	 */
499 	this.isMouseDownBtn = function(mouse) {
500 		var ret = mouseBtn[mouse];
501 		mouseBtn[mouse] = false;
502 		return ret;
503 	};
504 	
505 	/**
506 	 * Gets the mouse's current X Position.
507 	 * @returns {Number} the x position.
508 	 */
509 	this.getMouseX = function() {
510 		return mousePos.x;
511 	};
512 	
513 	/**
514 	 * Gets the mouse's current Y Position.
515 	 * @returns {Number} the y position.
516 	 */
517 	this.getMouseY = function() {
518 		return mousePos.y;
519 	};
520 	
521 	/**
522 	 * Sets this input handler to be listening in for mouse events on a given DOM object.
523 	 * Note that this method can only be called once, trying to attach to two objects results in a noop.
524 	 * @param {Node} dom the dom object to attach to.
525 	 */
526 	this.attachMouseListener = function(dom) {
527 		if (attached) return;
528 		
529 		dom.onmousemove = function(e) {
530 			mousePos.x = e.offsetX;
531 			mousePos.y = e.offsetY;
532 		};
533 		
534 		document.onmousedown = function(e) {
535 			mouseState[e.which] = true;
536 			mouseBtn[e.which] = true;
537 		};
538 		
539 		document.onmouseup = function(e) {
540 			mouseState[e.which] = false;
541 			mouseBtn[e.which] = false;
542 		};
543 		
544 		attached = true;
545 	};
546 };
547

551 GenericStar.Input.Mouse = {

555 /**
556  * This is a list of keys you can use with GenericStar.Input methods.
557  */

579 /**
580  * Creates a Sound Handler.
581  * @class this class manages sounds, allowing for playback.
582  */
583 GenericStar.Sound = function() {
584 	var self = this;
585 	
586 	/**
587 	 * Plays a given sound once.
588 	 * @param {String} url the URL of the sound to play (mp3 or ogg)
589 	 * @param {Number} [volume=1] the volume of the sound to play from 0 (softest) to 1 (loudest)
590 	 * @param {Number} [startTime=0] where in the sound to start playing from
591 	 */
592 	this.playSound = function(url, volume, startTime) {
593 		if (volume == undefined) volume = 1;
594 		if (startTime == undefined) startTime = 0;
595 		volume = volume < 0 ? 0 : volume > 1 ? 1 : volume;
596 		
597 		var sound = document.createElement('audio'); 
598 		
599 		sound.addEventListener('canplaythrough',function() {
600 			sound.currentTime = startTime;
601 			sound.volume = volume;
602 			sound.play();
603 		},false);
604 		
605 		sound.addEventListener('ended',function() {
606 			sound.src = "";
607 			sound = null;
608 		},false);
609 		
610 		sound.src = url;
611 		sound.load();
612 	};
613 	
614 	var bgrndMusic = new Array();
615 	
616 	/**
617 	 * Gets the allocated background music from a given URL.
618 	 * This music object can then be manipulated by calling other methods in this object.
619 	 * @param {String} url the url to fetch the music from
620 	 * @returns {Audio} the audio object representing the music, or undefined / null if it is not loaded
621 	 */
622 	this.getMusic = function(url) {
623 		if (bgrndMusic[url] == undefined || bgrndMusic[url] == null) {
624 			self.createSound(url, function(snd) {
625 				bgrndMusic[url] = snd;
626 			});
627 		}
628 		
629 		return bgrndMusic[url];
630 	};
631 	
632 	/**
633 	 * Creates an HTML5 Audio Object. For memory reasons, it is often
634 	 * better to use playSound and getBackgroundMusic rather than ever
635 	 * try to use this method.
636 	 * @param {String} url the url to download the music from
637 	 * @param {Function} callback {(Audio):()} this function is called back when the audio is loaded
638 	 */
639 	this.createSound = function(url, callback) {
640 		var sound = document.createElement('audio'); 
641 		sound.addEventListener('canplaythrough',function() {
642 			if (callback !== null && callback !== undefined) callback(sound);
643 		},false);
644 		
645 		sound.src = url;
646 		sound.load();
647 	};
648 	
649 	/**
650 	 * Plays an Audio Object (from createSound or getMusic).
651 	 * If the sound is already playing, this method does nothing.
652 	 * @param {Audio} sound the sound to play.
653 	 * @param {Boolean} [repeat] if true, repeat the audio. If not set, will not change repeat amount.
654 	 */
655 	this.play = function(sound, repeat) {
656 		if (repeat != undefined && repeat != null) self.setRepeat(sound, repeat);
657 		sound.play();
658 	};
659 	
660 	/**
661 	 * Pauses an Audio Object (from createSound or getMusic).
662 	 * If the sound is already paused, this method does nothing.
663 	 * @param {Audio} sound the sound to pause
664 	 */
665 	this.pause = function(sound) {
666 		sound.pause();
667 	};
668 	
669 	/**
670 	 * Stops and Audio Object (from createSound or getMusic).
671 	 * This is the same as calling pause and setting current time to 0 seconds.
672 	 * @param {Audio} sound the sound to stop
673 	 */
674 	this.stop = function(sound) {
675 		sound.pause();
676 		self.setCurrentTime(sound, 0);
677 	};
678 	
679 	/**
680 	 * Gets whether or not a given sound (from createSound or getMusic) is playing.
681 	 * @returns {Boolean} true if it is playing, false otherwise
682 	 */
683 	this.isPlaying = function(sound) {
684 		return sound.paused == false;
685 	};
686 	
687 	/**
688 	 * Sets whether or not this sound will repeat when played.
689 	 * @param {Audio} sound the sound to set
690 	 * @param {Boolean} repeat true if we want to repeat
691 	 */
692 	this.setRepeat = function(sound, repeat) {
693 		sound.loop = repeat;
694 	};
695 	
696 	/**
697 	 * Sets the current playback position in the sound.
698 	 * @param {Audio} sound a sound object
699 	 * @param {Number} time the time (in seconds) to jump to
700 	 */
701 	this.setCurrentTime = function(sound, time) {
702 		sound.currentTime = time;
703 	};
704 	
705 	/**
706 	 * Sets the volume of a given sound.
707 	 * @param {Audio} sound the sound to set volume of
708 	 * @param {Number} volume the volume to be from 0 (softest) to 1 (loudest)
709 	 */
710 	this.setVolume = function(sound, volume) {
711 		sound.volume = volume;
712 	};
713 };

717 /**
718  * Creates a physics controller.
719  * @class This is a wrapper for Box2D, and as such is best for 2D physics simulations.
720  * @param {GenericStar.Core} core the core controller of the game
721  * @param gravity the gravity vector for this world
722  * @param {Number} gravity.x the x component of the gravity for this world
723  * @param {Number} gravity.y the y component of the gravity for this world
724  */
725 GenericStar.Physics.Controller = function(core, gravity) {
726 	var SCALE = 1.0/30.0;
727 	
728 	//namespaces
729 	var b2Vec2 = Box2D.Common.Math.b2Vec2,
730 	    b2BodyDef = Box2D.Dynamics.b2BodyDef,
731  	    b2Body = Box2D.Dynamics.b2Body,
732  	    b2FixtureDef = Box2D.Dynamics.b2FixtureDef,
733  	    b2Fixture = Box2D.Dynamics.b2Fixture,
734  	    b2World = Box2D.Dynamics.b2World,
735  	    b2MassData = Box2D.Collision.Shapes.b2MassData,
736  	    b2PolygonShape = Box2D.Collision.Shapes.b2PolygonShape,
737  	    b2CircleShape = Box2D.Collision.Shapes.b2CircleShape,
738         b2DebugDraw = Box2D.Dynamics.b2DebugDraw,
739         
740         b2RevoluteJointDef = Box2D.Dynamics.Joints.b2RevoluteJointDef,
741         b2DistanceJointDef = Box2D.Dynamics.Joints.b2DistanceJointDef,
742         b2PulleyJointDef   = Box2D.Dynamics.Joints.b2PulleyJointDef,
743         b2GearJointDef     = Box2D.Dynamics.Joints.b2GearJointDef;
744 	
745 	
746 	var world = new b2World(
747             new b2Vec2(gravity.x * SCALE, gravity.y * SCALE)
748          ,  true                 //allow sleep
749       );
750 	
751 	var contactListener = function() {
752 		this.BeginContact = function(contact) {};
753 		this.EndContact = function(contact) {};
754 		this.PreSolve = function(contact, oldManifold) {};
755 		this.PostSolve = function(contact, impulse) {};
756 	};
757 	
758 	var isCcw = function(p1, p2, p3) {
759 		return (p2.x - p1.x)*(p3.y - p1.y) - (p2.y - p1.y)*(p3.x - p1.x) > 0;
760 	};
761 	
762 	world.SetContactListener(new contactListener());
763 	
764 	/*var debugDraw = new b2DebugDraw();
765 	debugDraw.SetSprite(document.getElementById("debug").getContext("2d"));
766 	debugDraw.SetDrawScale(30.0);
767 	debugDraw.SetFillAlpha(0.3);
768 	debugDraw.SetLineThickness(1.0);
769 	debugDraw.SetFlags(b2DebugDraw.e_shapeBit | b2DebugDraw.e_jointBit);
770 	world.SetDebugDraw(debugDraw);*/
771 	
772 	this.stepSimulation = function() {
773 		world.Step(1.0/30, 1, 1);
774 		world.ClearForces();
775 		world.DrawDebugData();
776 	};
777 	
778 	var createBody = function(x, y, free, bullet, canRotate, damping, angularDamping) {
779 		if (bullet == undefined) bullet = false;
780 		if (canRotate == undefined) canRotate = true;
781 		
782 		var bodyDef = new b2BodyDef;
783 		bodyDef.position.x = x;
784         bodyDef.position.y = y;
785 		if (!free) bodyDef.type = b2Body.b2_staticBody;
786 		else bodyDef.type = b2Body.b2_dynamicBody;
787         if (damping != undefined) bodyDef.linearDamping = damping * SCALE;
788         if (angularDamping != undefined) bodyDef.angularDamping = angularDamping * SCALE;
789         bodyDef.fixedRotation = !canRotate;
790         bodyDef.bullet = bullet;
791         var created = world.CreateBody(bodyDef);
792         return created;
793 	};
794 	
795 	var setupFixture = function(solid, friction, density, restitution) {
796 		var fixDef = new b2FixtureDef;
797 		fixDef.isSensor = !solid;
798 		fixDef.friction = friction;
799         fixDef.density = density;
800         fixDef.restitution = restitution;
801         return fixDef;
802 	};
803 	
804 	/**
805 	 * Creates a box physics object
806 	 * @param {Number} x the x position of the top left of the box
807 	 * @param {Number} y the y position of the top left of the box
808 	 * @param {Number} width how wide the box is
809 	 * @param {Number} height how tall the box is
810 	 * @param {Boolean} free if true, this object can move, otherwise it will be immobile
811 	 * @param {Boolean} solid if true, this object will not pass through other solid objects
812 	 * @param {Boolean} [bullet=false] if true, this object will be more rigerously collision checked, but may slow the game down.
813 	 * 					Use for objects that are passing through other objects.
814 	 * @param {Boolean} [canRotate=true] if false, this object cannot rotate
815 	 * @param {Number} [damping] how much "air resistance" there is (friction to general movement). If undefined, no damping will occur.
816 	 * @param {Number} [friction=0.5] the coefficient of friction this object has
817 	 * @param {Number} [density=1.0] the density of this object
818 	 * @param {Number} [restitution=0.3] the "bounciness" of this object
819 	 * @returns {GenericStar.Physics.PhysObj} the created physics object
820 	 */
821 	this.createBox = function(x, y, width, height, free, solid, bullet, canRotate, damping, friction, density, restitution) {
822 		if (friction == undefined) friction = 0.5;
823 		if (density == undefined) density = 1.0;
824 		if (restitution == undefined) restitution = 0.3;
825 		width = width * SCALE;
826 		height = height * SCALE;
827 		x = x * SCALE + width / 2;
828 		y = y * SCALE + height / 2;
829 		
830 		var created = createBody(x, y, free, bullet, canRotate, damping);
831         
832         var fixDef = setupFixture(solid, friction, density, restitution);
833         fixDef.shape = new b2PolygonShape;
834         fixDef.shape.SetAsBox(width/2, height/2);
835         created.CreateFixture(fixDef);
836 		
837         var boxRet = new GenericStar.Physics.PhysObj(created, this, width, height, true);
838 		return boxRet;
839 	};
840 	
841 	/**
842 	 * Creates a circular physics object
843 	 * @param {Number} x the x position of the center of the circle
844 	 * @param {Number} y the y position of the center of the circle
845 	 * @param {Number} radius the radius of the circle
846 	 * @param {Boolean} free if true, this object can move, otherwise it will be immobile
847 	 * @param {Boolean} solid if true, this object will not pass through other solid objects
848 	 * @param {Boolean} [bullet=false] if true, this object will be more rigerously collision checked, but may slow the game down.
849 	 * 					Use for objects that are passing through other objects.
850 	 * @param {Boolean} [canRotate=true] if false, this object cannot rotate
851 	 * @param {Number} [damping] how much "air resistance" there is (friction to general movement). If undefined, no damping will occur.
852 	 * @param {Number} [friction=0.5] the coefficient of friction this object has
853 	 * @param {Number} [density=1.0] the density of this object
854 	 * @param {Number} [restitution=0.3] the "bounciness" of this object
855 	 * @returns {GenericStar.Physics.PhysObj} the created physics object
856 	 */
857 	this.createCircle = function(x, y, radius, free, solid, bullet, canRotate, damping, friction, density, restitution) {
858 		if (density == undefined) density = 1.0;
859 		if (friction == undefined) friction = 0.5;
860 		if (restitution == undefined) restitution = 0.3;
861 		radius = radius * SCALE;
862 		x = x * SCALE;
863 		y = y * SCALE;
864 		
865 		var created = createBody(x, y, free, bullet, canRotate, damping);
866 		
867 		var fixDef = setupFixture(solid, friction, density, restitution);
868         fixDef.shape = new b2CircleShape;
869         fixDef.shape.SetRadius(radius);
870         created.CreateFixture(fixDef);
871         
872         return new GenericStar.Physics.PhysObj(created, this, radius*2, radius*2, true);
873 	};
874 	
875 	/**
876 	 * Creates a polygonal physics object
877 	 * @param {Number} x the x position of the center of this object
878 	 * @param {Number} y the y position of the center of this object
879 	 * @param {Point[][]} triangles List of triangles to defined the solid portion of the
880 	 * 			polygon. Note that a triangle itself is an array of three points (where a point is an
881 	 * 			object containing an x and y attribute)
882 	 * @param {Boolean} free if true, this object can move and observe dynamics, otherwise it is pinned to the scene and cannot move.
883 	 * @param {Boolean} solid if true, this object will never pass through other solid objects
884 	 * @param {Boolean} [bullet=false] if true, this object will be more rigerously collision checked, but may slow the game down.
885 	 * 					Use for objects that are passing through other objects.
886 	 * @param {Boolean} [canRotate=true] if false, this object cannot rotate
887 	 * @param {Number} [damping] how much "air resistance" there is (friction to general movement). If undefined, no damping will occur.
888 	 * @param {Number} [friction=0.5] the coefficient of friction for this object (0.3 generally works)
889 	 * @param {Number} [density=1.0] the density of this object.
890 	 * @param {Number} [restitution=0.3] the "bounciness" of this object
891 	 * @returns {GenericStar.Physics.PhysObj} the physics object created
892 	 */
893 	this.createPolygon = function(x, y, triangles, free, solid, bullet, canRotate, damping, friction, density, restitution) {
894 		if (friction == undefined) friction = 0.5;
895 		if (density == undefined) density = 1.0;
896 		if (restitution == undefined) restitution = 0.3;
897 		x = x * SCALE;
898 		y = y * SCALE;
899 		
900 		var minPt = {x: triangles[0][0].x, y: triangles[0][0].y};
901 		var maxPt = {x: triangles[0][0].x, y: triangles[0][0].y};
902 		
903 		var created = createBody(x, y, free, bullet, canRotate, damping);
904         
905         for(var i=0; i < triangles.length; i++) {
906         	var fixDef = setupFixture(solid, friction, density, restitution);
907             fixDef.shape = new b2PolygonShape;
908             if (core.DEBUG && triangles[i].length != 3) {
909             	console.warn("WARNING physics triangle list malformed at position["+i+"], data:["+triangles+"]");
910             	continue;
911             }
912             var ccw = isCcw(triangles[i][0], triangles[i][1], triangles[i][2]);
913             var arr = new Array();
914             for(var j=0; j < 3; j++) {
915             	var ind = ccw ? j : 2 - j;
916             	minPt.x = Math.min(minPt.x, triangles[i][j].x);
917             	minPt.y = Math.min(minPt.y, triangles[i][j].y);
918             	maxPt.x = Math.max(maxPt.x, triangles[i][j].x);
919             	maxPt.y = Math.max(maxPt.y, triangles[i][j].y);
920             	arr[ind] = new b2Vec2(triangles[i][j].x * SCALE, triangles[i][j].y * SCALE);
921             }
922             fixDef.shape.SetAsArray(arr, 3);
923             
924             created.CreateFixture(fixDef);
925         }
926 		
927 		return new GenericStar.Physics.PhysObj(created, this, (maxPt.x - minPt.x)*SCALE, (maxPt.y - minPt.y)*SCALE, false);
928 	};
929 	
930 	/**
931 	 * Pins a distance joint between two physics objects (a distance between two points on
932 	 * two objects cannot exceed whatever you set).
933 	 * @param {GenericStar.Physics.PhysObj} phys1 the first physics object to tie together
934 	 * @param pos1 the position in world-space to tie the first object to
935 	 * @param {Number} pos1.x the x coordinate of the first position
936 	 * @param {Number} pos1.y the y coordinate of the first position
937 	 * @param {GenericStar.Physics.PhysObj} phys2 the second physics object to tie to the first
938 	 * @param pos2 the position in world-space to tie the second object to
939 	 * @param {Number} pos2.x the x coordinate of the second position
940 	 * @param {Number} pos2.y the y coordinate of the second position
941 	 * @param {Number} dist the distance that these two objects cannot exceed
942 	 * @param {Boolean} [collide=true] whether or not phys1 interacts with phys2 anymore
943 	 * @param {Number} [dampeningFrequency] the frequency at which dampening occurs. If undefined, there will be no dampening. 
944 	 * @param {Number} [dampeningRatio] number in between 0 and 1.0 that corresponds to the dampening ration. If undefined, there will be no dampening.
945 	 * @returns {GenericStar.Physics.Joint} the joint that was created.
946 	 */
947 	this.pinDistanceJoint = function(phys1, pos1, phys2, pos2, dist, collide, dampeningFrequency, dampeningRatio) {
948 		var jointDef = new b2DistanceJointDef;
949 		var worldPos1 = phys1._body.GetWorldPoint(new b2Vec2(0,0));
950 		var worldPos2 = phys2._body.GetWorldPoint(new b2Vec2(0,0));
951 		
952 		if (pos1 == undefined) pos1 = {x: worldPos1.x/SCALE, y: worldPos1.y/SCALE};
953 		if (pos2 == undefined) pos2 = {x: worldPos2.x/SCALE, y: worldPos2.y/SCALE};
954 		if (collide == undefined) collide = true;
955 		
956 		jointDef.Initialize(phys1._body, phys2._body, 
957 				new b2Vec2(pos1.x*SCALE, pos1.y*SCALE),
958 				new b2Vec2(pos2.x*SCALE, pos2.y*SCALE));
959 		
960 		jointDef.length = dist * SCALE;
961 		jointDef.collideConnected = collide;
962 		if (dampeningFrequency != undefined && dampeningRatio != undefined) {
963 			jointDef.frequencyHz = dampeningFrequency;
964 			jointDef.dampingRatio = dampeningRatio;
965 		}
966 		
967 		var joint = world.CreateJoint(jointDef);
968 		return new GenericStar.Physics.Joint(joint, false, false);
969 	};
970 	
971 	/**
972 	 * Pins a revolute joint between two physics object.
973 	 * @param {GenericStar.Physics.PhysObj} phys1 the second object to pin
974 	 * @param {GenericStar.Physics.PhysObj} phys2 the second object to pin
975 	 * @param pos the location in world-coordinates to pin both objects to
976 	 * @param {Number} pos.x the x component of the object pinning position
977 	 * @param {Number} pos.y the y component of the object pinning position
978 	 * @param [angleConstraints] angles the joint must stay within. If not included, default is no restrictions.
979 	 * @param {Number} [angleConstraints.min] minimum angle the joint can have (in degrees)
980 	 * @param {Number} [angleConstraints.max] maximum angle the joint can have (in degrees)
981 	 * @param {Number} [maxMotorTorque] the maximum torque the motor powering the joint will have.
982 	 * 			If it is undefined, this joint will not have a motor.
983 	 * @returns {GenericStar.Physics.Joint} the joint that was created.
984 	 */
985 	this.pinRevoluteJoint = function(phys1, phys2, pos, angleConstraints, maxMotorTorque) {
986 		var jointDef = new b2RevoluteJointDef;
987 		jointDef.Initialize(phys1._body, phys2._body, new b2Vec2(pos.x*SCALE, pos.y*SCALE));
988 		
989 		if (angleConstraints != undefined && angleConstraints.min != undefined && angleConstraints.max != undefined) {
990 			jointDef.lowerAngle = angleConstraints.min * Math.PI / 180;
991 			jointDef.upperAngle = angleConstraints.max * Math.PI / 180;
992 			jointDef.enableLimit = true;
993 		}
994 		
995 		if (maxMotorTorque != undefined && maxMotorTorque != null) {
996 			jointDef.maxMotorTorque = maxMotorTorque;
997 			jointDef.motorSpeed = 0.0;
998 			jointDef.enableMotor = true;
999 		} else {
1000 			jointDef.enableMotor = false;
1001 		}
1002 		
1003 		var joint = world.CreateJoint(jointDef);
1004 		
1005 		return new GenericStar.Physics.Joint(joint, jointDef.enableMotor, true);
1006 	};
1007 	
1008 	/**
1009 	 * Creates a pully joint between two objects (simulates two objects attached to
1010 	 * a pully system).
1011 	 * @param {GenericStar.Physics.PhysObj} phys1 the first object to attach to the pully
1012 	 * @param pullyTopPos1 the location in world-coordinates of the top of the pully attached to phys1
1013 	 * @param {Number} pullyTopPos1.x the x component of the first pulley top
1014 	 * @param {Number} pullyTopPos1.y the y component of the first pulley top
1015 	 * @param attachPos1 the location in world-coordinates of where the string is attached to phys1 (point should be on phys1)
1016 	 * @param {Number} attachPos1.x the x component of the first pulley attach position
1017 	 * @param {Number} attachPos1.y the y component of the first pulley attach position
1018 	 * @param {GenericStar.Physics.PhysObj} phys2 the second object to attach to the pully
1019 	 * @param pullyTopPos2 the location in world-coordinates of the top of the pully attached to phys2
1020 	 * @param {Number} pullyTopPos2.x the x component of the second pulley top
1021 	 * @param {Number} pullyTopPos2.y the y component of the second pulley top
1022 	 * @param attachPos2 the location in world-coordinates of where the string is attached to phys2 (point should be on phys2)
1023 	 * @param {Number} attachPos2.x the x component of the second pulley attach position
1024 	 * @param {Number} attachPos2.y the y component of the second pulley attach position
1025 	 * @param [maxLength1] the maximum distance that the pulley attached to phys1 can reach
1026 	 * @param [maxLength2] the maximum distance that the pulley attached to phys2 can reach
1027 	 * @param [ratio=1] the ratio of lengths the pully can achieve
1028 	 * @returns {GenericStar.Physics.Joint} the joint that was created.
1029 	 */
1030 	this.pinPulleyJoint = function(phys1, pullyTopPos1, attachPos1, phys2, pullyTopPos2, attachPos2, maxLength1, maxLength2, ratio) {
1031 		var anchor1 = new b2Vec2(pullyTopPos1.x * SCALE, pullyTopPos1.y * SCALE);
1032 		var anchor2 = new b2Vec2(pullyTopPos2.x * SCALE, pullyTopPos2.y * SCALE);
1033 		var pos1 = new b2Vec2(attachPos1.x * SCALE, attachPos1.y * SCALE);
1034 		var pos2 = new b2Vec2(attachPos2.x * SCALE, attachPos2.y * SCALE);
1035 		var maxLength = Math.sqrt(Math.pow(pos1.x - anchor1.x, 2) + Math.pow(pos1.y - anchor1.y, 2)) +
1036 						Math.sqrt(Math.pow(pos2.x - anchor2.x, 2) + Math.pow(pos2.y - anchor2.y, 2)) - (1*SCALE);
1037 		
1038 		if (maxLength1 == undefined) maxLength1 = maxLength;
1039 		else maxLength1 *= SCALE;
1040 		maxLength1 = Math.min(maxLength1, maxLength);
1041 		
1042 		if (maxLength2 == undefined) maxLength2 = maxLength;
1043 		else maxLength2 *= SCALE;
1044 		maxLength2 = Math.min(maxLength2, maxLength);
1045 		
1046 		if (ratio == undefined) ratio = 1.0;
1047 
1048 		var jointDef = new b2PulleyJointDef;
1049 
1050 		jointDef.Initialize(phys1._body, phys2._body, anchor1, anchor2, pos1, pos2, ratio);
1051 		jointDef.maxLengthA = maxLength1;
1052 		jointDef.maxLengthB = maxLength2;
1053 		
1054 		var joint = world.CreateJoint(jointDef);
1055 		return new GenericStar.Physics.Joint(joint, false, false);
1056 	};
1057 	
1058 	/**
1059 	 * Pins a gear joint between two revolute joints (makes them locked to each
1060 	 * other's angle, times a given ratio).
1061 	 * @param {GenericStar.Physics.PhysObj} phys the first object attached to the first revolute joint
1062 	 * @param {GenericStar.Physics.Joint} joint1 the first revolute joint
1063 	 * @param {GenericStar.Physics.PhysObj} phys2 the second object attached to the second revolute joint
1064 	 * @param {GenericStar.Physics.Joint} joint2 the second revolute joint
1065 	 * @param {Number} ratio the number to multiply the first joint's angle by to get the second joint's angle
1066 	 * @returns {GenericStar.Physics.Joint} the joint that was created, or null if either joint was not a revolute joint
1067 	 */
1068 	this.pinGearJoint = function(phys, joint1, phys2, joint2, ratio) {
1069 		if (!joint1._gear || !joint2._gear) return null;
1070 		
1071 		var jointDef = new b2GearJointDef;
1072 		jointDef.joint1 = joint1._joint;
1073 		jointDef.joint2 = joint2._joint;
1074 		jointDef.bodyA = phys._body;
1075 		jointDef.bodyB = phys2._body;
1076 		jointDef.ratio = ratio;
1077 		
1078 		var joint = world.CreateJoint(jointDef);
1079 		return new GenericStar.Physics.Joint(joint, false, false);
1080 	};

1082 	/**
1083 	 * Creates a player physics object for a 2D Platformer.
1084 	 * @param {Number} x the x-coordinate the player starts at
1085 	 * @param {Number} y the y-coordinate the player starts at
1086 	 * @param {Number} w the width of the player. Note that it must be the case that width <= height.
1087 	 * @param {Number} h the height of the player. Note that it must be the case that height >= width.
1088 	 * @param [maxspeed] the maximum speed this player can travel at before being capped.
1089  	 * @param {Number} maxspeed.x x component of the maximum speed at which the player can travel
1090  	 * @param {Number} maxspeed.y y component of the maximum speed at which the player can travelmaxspeed
1091  	 * @param {Number} [airTravelFactor] the factor multiplied into walking speed while the player is in the air
1092 	 * @param {Number} [wallStick] the number of steps the player needs to hold the move key before unsticking from a wall
1093 	 * @param {Boolean} [wallAlign] if true, a player will not bounce off of walls
1094 	 * @param {Number} [wallReduce] the factor by which we reduce falling maxspeed while sliding down a wall
1095 	 * @param {Number} [jumpTime] the number of steps by which the player can extend the jump
1096 	 * @returns {GenericStar.Physics.Player} the created player object
1097 	 */
1098 	this.createPlayer = function(x, y, w, h, maxspeed, airTravelFactor, wallStick, wallAlign, wallReduce, jumpTime) {
1099 		if (w > h) {
1100 			if (core.DEBUG) console.error("Assertion[Player Width <= Height] Failed!");
1101 			w = h;
1102 		}
1103 		
1104 		if (maxspeed == undefined) maxspeed = {x:20 / SCALE, y:20 / SCALE};
1105 		if (airTravelFactor == undefined) airTravelFactor = 1;
1106 		if (wallStick == undefined) wallStick = 0;
1107 		if (wallAlign == undefined) wallAlign = true;
1108 		if (wallReduce == undefined) wallReduce = 1;
1109 		if (jumpTime == undefined) jumpTime = 4;
1110 		
1111 		wallReduce = Math.min(1.0, Math.max(0, wallReduce));
1112 		
1113 		var friction = 1;
1114 		var density = 0.1;
1115 		var restitution = 0.01;
1116 		x = x * SCALE;
1117 		y = y * SCALE;
1118 		
1119 		//create rectangle
1120 		var rectWidth = w * SCALE;
1121 		var rectHeight= h * SCALE - rectWidth/2;
1122 		var bodyRect = createBody(x + rectWidth/2, y + rectHeight/2, true, true, false, 0, 6);
1123         
1124         var fixDef = setupFixture(true, 0, density, restitution);
1125         fixDef.shape = new b2PolygonShape;
1126         fixDef.shape.SetAsBox(rectWidth/2, rectHeight/2);
1127         var fixRect = bodyRect.CreateFixture(fixDef);
1128         var fixRect = null;
1129 		
1130 		//create wheel
1131 		var radius = w * SCALE / 2;
1132 		var fixDef = setupFixture(true, friction, density, restitution);
1133         fixDef.shape = new b2CircleShape;
1134         fixDef.shape.SetRadius(radius);
1135         fixDef.shape.SetLocalPosition(new b2Vec2(0, rectHeight/2));
1136         var fixCircle = bodyRect.CreateFixture(fixDef);
1137         
1138         return new GenericStar.Physics.Player(bodyRect, fixRect, fixCircle, this, w*SCALE, h*SCALE, 
1139         		{x: maxspeed.x * SCALE, y: maxspeed.y * SCALE},
1140         		airTravelFactor, wallStick, !!wallAlign, wallReduce, jumpTime);
1141 	};

1446 /**
1447  * Makes the character jump. Note that this will make the character jump whether or not there
1448  * is ground under its feet - that check must be done manually.
1449  * @param {Number} dY the amount of force to apply vertically. Should be positive.
1450  * @param {Number} [dX] the amount of force to apply horizontally. Not required, useful for wall jumps.
1451  * @param {Boolean} [reset] if true, start a fresh jump now instead of making this function just extend the current jump
1452  */
1453 GenericStar.Physics.Player.prototype.jump = function(dY, dX, reset) {
1454 	//reset jump physics
1455 	if (reset != undefined && reset) {this._jumpTime = 0;}
1456 	this._prevJump = true;
1457 	if (this._jumpTime == 0) { //zero out the vertical velocity (keep x component)
1458 		this._body.m_linearVelocity.x = this._body.m_linearVelocity.x * this._vecRight.x;
1459 		this._body.m_linearVelocity.y = this._body.m_linearVelocity.y * this._vecRight.y;
1460 	}
1461 	
1462 	if (this._jumpTime > this._maxJumpTime) return;
1463 	
1464 	this._body.ApplyForce(new this.b2Vec2(this._vecUp.x * dY * this._phys.getScale(),
1465 											this._vecUp.y * dY * this._phys.getScale()),
1466 							this._body.GetWorldCenter());
1467 	
1468 	//apply horizontal forces (in x component)
1469 	if (dX != undefined && dX != 0) {
1470 		dX /= this._maxJumpTime;
1471 		this._body.ApplyImpulse(new this.b2Vec2(dX * this._vecRight.x * this._phys.getScale(),
1472 												dX * this._vecRight.x * this._phys.getScale()),
1473 								this._body.GetWorldCenter());
1474 	}
1475 	
1476 	this._jumpTime++;
1477 };

1479 /**
1480  * Makes the player walk to the left or right.
1481  * Walking can be affected by being in the air or being stuck on a wall,
1482  * so this has no guarantee of actually moving the player.
1483  * @param {Number} dX speed at which to walk. If negative, walk left. If positive, walk right.
1484  * @param {Boolean} [instantaneous=true] if true, the player can turn around instantly.
1485  * 			Otherwise, the player must slow down before turning around.
1486  */
1487 GenericStar.Physics.Player.prototype.walk = function(dX, instantaneous) {
1488 	if (dX == 0) {
1489 		this._prevWalk = 0;
1490 		return;
1491 	}
1492 	if (instantaneous == undefined) instantaneous = true;
1493 	this._prevWalk = dX > 0 ? 1 : dX < 0 ? -1 : 0;
1494 	
1495 	var air = this._onGround ? 1 : this._airTravelFactor;
1496 	
1497 	if ((this._wallToLeft  && this._wallUnstick >  this._wallStick) ||
1498 		(this._wallToRight && this._wallUnstick < -this._wallStick) || 
1499 		(!this._wallToLeft && !this._wallToRight) ||
1500 		this._onGround) {
1501 		
1502 		
1503 		if (instantaneous) {
1504 			this._body.m_linearVelocity.x =
1505 				this._vecRight.x * dX * this._phys.getScale() * air + this._body.m_linearVelocity.x * Math.abs(this._vecUp.x);
1506 			this._body.m_linearVelocity.y =
1507 				this._vecRight.y * dX * this._phys.getScale() * air + this._body.m_linearVelocity.y * Math.abs(this._vecUp.y);
1508 		} else {
1509 			this._body.ApplyForce(new this.b2Vec2(
1510 					this._vecRight.x * dX * this._phys.getScale() * air,
1511 					this._vecRight.y * dX * this._phys.getScale() * air),
1512 				  this._body.GetWorldCenter());
1513 		}
1514 	}
1515 };
1516 
1517 GenericStar.Physics.Player.prototype.step = function(print) {
1518 	//this._body.m_sweep.a = 0;//This is what stops the player from rotating. That or magic.
1519 	
1520 	if  (this._prevJump == false) this._jumpTime = 0;
1521 	
1522 	var stepDotWithin = function(x, y, neg, variance) {
1523 		var dot = neg * x.x * y.x + neg * x.y * y.y;
1524 		return dot > 1 - variance && dot < 1 + variance;
1525 	};
1526 	
1527 	//calculate player state
1528 	var prevState = this._state;
1529 	var cl = this._body.GetContactList();
1530 	this._wallToLeft = false;
1531 	this._wallToRight = false;
1532 	this._onGround = false;
1533 	for(var i=0, listMax=100; cl != null && i < listMax; i++, cl = cl.next) {
1534 		if (cl.contact.IsTouching() && !cl.contact.IsSensor()) {
1535 			var manifold = new Box2D.Collision.b2WorldManifold;
1536 			cl.contact.GetWorldManifold(manifold);
1537 			var norm = {x: manifold.m_normal.x, y: manifold.m_normal.y};
1538 			if (cl.contact.GetFixtureB() == this._fixBot || cl.contact.GetFixtureB() == this._fixTop) {
1539 				norm.x *= -1;
1540 				norm.y *= -1;
1541 			}
1542 			this._wallToLeft = this._wallToLeft  || stepDotWithin(norm, this._vecRight,-1, this.MAX_WALL_ANGLE);
1543 			this._wallToRight= this._wallToRight || stepDotWithin(norm, this._vecRight, 1, this.MAX_WALL_ANGLE);
1544 			this._onGround   = this._onGround    || stepDotWithin(norm, this._vecUp,   -1, this.MAX_GROUND_ANGLE);
1545 		}
1546 	}
1547 	
1548 	//if (print) console.log(this._wallToLeft+", "+this._wallToRight+", "+this._onGround);
1549 	
1550 	//align (magnet) to walls
1551 	var effectiveTopspeedVert = 1;
1552 	if (this._wallMagnetism > 0 && (this._wallToLeft || this._wallToRight) && !this._onGround) {
1553 		
1554 		if (this._wallToLeft && this._wallUnstick < this._wallStick) {
1555 			this._body.ApplyForce(new this.b2Vec2(
1556 					this._wallMagnetism * -this._vecRight.x,
1557 					this._wallMagnetism * -this._vecRight.y),
1558 				this._body.GetWorldCenter());
1559 			
1560 		} else if (this._wallToRight && this._wallUnstick > -this._wallStick) {
1561 			this._body.ApplyForce(new this.b2Vec2(
1562 					this._wallMagnetism * this._vecRight.x,
1563 					this._wallMagnetism * this._vecRight.y),
1564 				this._body.GetWorldCenter());
1565 		}
1566 		
1567 		effectiveTopspeedVert = this._wallReduce;
1568 	}
1569 	
1570 	//sticky walls
1571 	if (this._prevWalk < 0 && this._wallUnstick > 0) this._wallUnstick = 0;
1572 	if (this._prevWalk > 0 && this._wallUnstick < 0) this._wallUnstick = 0;
1573 	this._wallUnstick += this._prevWalk;
1574 	this._prevWalk = 0;
1575 	
1576 	//cap topspeed
1577 	var linVel = {x: this._body.m_linearVelocity.x, y: this._body.m_linearVelocity.y};
1578 	var speedX = linVel.x * this._vecRight.x + linVel.y * this._vecRight.y;
1579 	var speedY =-linVel.x * this._vecUp.x    - linVel.y * this._vecUp.y;
1580 	speedX = Math.max(-this._maxSpeed.x, Math.min(this._maxSpeed.x, speedX));
1581 	var yComp = {
1582 		x: linVel.x * Math.abs(this._vecUp.x),
1583 		y: linVel.y * Math.abs(this._vecUp.y)
1584 	};
1585 	var yCompMag = Math.sqrt(yComp.x * yComp.x + yComp.y * yComp.y);
1586 	yComp.x /= yCompMag;
1587 	yComp.y /= yCompMag;
1588 	if (stepDotWithin(yComp, this._vecUp, 1, 0.1)) {
1589 		speedY = Math.max(-this._maxSpeed.y, Math.min(this._maxSpeed.y, speedY));
1590 	} else {
1591 		speedY = Math.max(-this._maxSpeed.y * effectiveTopspeedVert,
1592 				 Math.min( this._maxSpeed.y * effectiveTopspeedVert, speedY));
1593 	}
1594 	
1595 	this._body.m_linearVelocity.x = speedX * this._vecRight.x - speedY * this._vecUp.x;
1596 	this._body.m_linearVelocity.y = speedX * this._vecRight.y - speedY * this._vecUp.y;
1597 	
1598 	this._prevJump = false;
1599 };

1732  * @param {String} dom.value the value to restrict

1831 /**
1832  * Runs an ajax command.
1833  * @param {Object} parameters the objects to send (using JSON)
1834  * @param {Function} callback the function to call on completion. It is
1835  * 			given a single argument containing the reply text.
1836  * @param {String} [url="action"] the url to call
1837  * @param {String} [contentType="application/x-www-form-urlencoded"] the content type of this request
1838  * @param {Boolean} [asBinary=false] if true, send data as binary
1839  * @param {Function} [progress] a function to call when the upload makes progress. One argument
1840  * 			is given, a Number from 0 to 1 representing percentage complete.
1841  */
1842 GenericStar.Editor.Library.prototype.ajax = function(parameters, callback, url, contentType, asBinary, progress) {
1843 	if (url === undefined || url === null) url = "action";
1844 	
1845 	if (contentType === undefined || contentType === null) {
1846 		contentType = "application/x-www-form-urlencoded";
1847 	}
1848 	if (asBinary === undefined || asBinary === null) asBinary = false;
1849 	
1850 	var xmlhttp;
1851 	if (window.XMLHttpRequest) {
1852 		xmlhttp = new XMLHttpRequest();
1853 	} else {
1854 		xmlhttp = new ActiveXObject("Microsoft.XMLHTTP");
1855 	}
1856 	xmlhttp.onreadystatechange = function() {
1857 		if (xmlhttp.readyState == 4 && xmlhttp.status == 200) {
1858 			callback(xmlhttp.responseText);
1859 		}
1860 	};
1861 	
1862 	if (progress !== undefined && progress !== null) {
1863 		xmlhttp.upload.addEventListener("progress", progress, false);
1864 	}
1865 	
1866 	xmlhttp.open("POST", "../../"+url, true);
1867 	xmlhttp.setRequestHeader("content-type", contentType);
1868 	if (!asBinary) {
1869 		xmlhttp.send(JSON.stringify(parameters));
1870 	} else {
1871 		xmlhttp.sendAsBinary(parameters);
1872 	}
1873 };

1917 /**
1918  * Creates a new clickaway handler.
1919  * @class This class handles listening to clicks anywhere and executing
1920  * 		clickaway events for registered objects.
1921  */
1922 GenericStar.Editor.ClickawayHandler = function() {
1923 	var cwid = 0;
1924 	
1925 	var domReactions = new Array();
1926 	
1927 	var triggerClickaway = function(ignore) {
1928 		for(var i=0; i < domReactions.length; i++) {
1929 			if (domReactions[i].dom !== ignore) domReactions[i].action();
1930 		}
1931 	};
1932 	
1933 	window.onclick = function(e) {
1934 		triggerClickaway(null);
1935 	};
1936 	
1937 	this.addClickaway = function(dom, func, onclick) {
1938 		if (dom.id === undefined || dom.id === null || dom.id === "") {
1939 			dom.id = "clickawayAutoId"+cwid;
1940 			cwid += 1;
1941 		}
1942 		domReactions.push({dom: dom, action: func});
1943 		this.addException(dom, dom, onclick);
1944 	};
1945 	
1946 	this.addException = function(domClick, domExcepted, onclick) {
1947 		domClick.addEventListener("click", function(e) {
1948 			e.stopPropagation();
1949 			if (onclick !== undefined) onclick(e);
1950 			triggerClickaway(domExcepted);
1951 		}, false);
1952 	};
1953 	
1954 
1955 	this.removeClickaway = function(dom) {
1956 		for(var i = 0; i < domReactions.length; i++) {
1957 			if (domReactions[i] === dom) {
1958 				domReactions.splice(i, 1);
1959 				i--;
1960 			}
1961 		}
1962 	};
1963 	
1964 	this.simulateClickaway = function() {
1965 		triggerClickaway(null);
1966 	};
1967 };

2031  */
2032 GenericStar.Editor.DropTarget = function(domDrop, descType, objectName, fileRestriction, domBubble, domBtn, domThrobber, notify, loader) {
2033 	var files = new Object();
2034 	
2035 	var domLib = new GenericStar.Editor.DomHelper();

2056 		}, true);

2058 			domLib.remClass(btns, "menuDroppedFileActionsOver");
2059 		}, true);

2062 		remBtn.className = "button2";
2063 		remBtn.innerHTML = "Remove";
2064 		remBtn.addEventListener("click", function(e) {
2065 			domLib.addTransitionCallback(node, function() {

3568 GenericStar.Editor.ReverseKeyMap.prototype.getKeyString = function(keycode) {
3569 	if (keycode === undefined) return null;
3570 	
3571 	if (keycode >= 65  && keycode <= 90)  return String.fromCharCode(keycode);
3572 	if (keycode >= 48  && keycode <= 57)  return ""+(keycode - 48);
3573 	if (keycode >= 96  && keycode <= 105) return "NumPad "+(keycode-96);
3574 	if (keycode >= 112 && keycode <= 123) return "F"+(keycode-111);
3575 	
3576 	return this.remainingKeyStrings[""+keycode];
3577 };

3585 	"37": "Left", "38": "Up", "39": "Right", "40": "Down",
3586 	"45": "Insert", "46": "Delete",
3587 	"91": "Windows",

3855 /**
3856  * Creates a copy of this object with the unique variables copied.
3857  * Note that this ignores the child (thus should not be called by a psuedo-instance)
3858  * @param {Object} the object to copy unique variables from (optional, if not included, uses this)
3859  * @returns {GenericStar.Editor.Generics.Generic} the new generic
3860  */
3861 GenericStar.Editor.Generics.Generic.prototype.generate = function(obj) {
3862 	var ret = this.getSelf();
3863 	if (!obj) obj = this;
3864 	for(var name in this.template) {
3865 		if (obj[name] !== ret[name]) ret[name] = obj[name];
3866 	}
3867 	return ret;
3868 };

3879 /**
3880  * Updates this object's values to refelect a change in resources.
3881  * @param {String} type the type of resource change (either "sprite" or "sound")
3882  * @param {GenericStar.Editor.Sidebar.DataChangeEvent} event the data that was changed
3883  * @returns {Boolean} true if any parameter was updated as a result of this event, false
3884  * 		if the object was not changed.
3885  */
3886 GenericStar.Editor.Generics.Generic.prototype.updatePointers = function(type, event) {
3887 	var changed = false;
3888 	var Dce = GenericStar.Editor.Sidebar.DataChangeEvent;
3889 	for(var name in this.template) {
3890 		var datatype = this.template[name].input.type;
3891 		if (datatype === type && this.getP(name) !== null && this.getP(name).url === event.name1) {
3892 			if (event.type === Dce.RENAME) this.getP(name).url = event.name2;
3893 			if (event.type === Dce.DELETE) this.setP(name, null);
3894 			
3895 			changed = changed || (event.type === Dce.RENAME) || (event.type === Dce.DELETE);
3896 		}
3897 	}
3898 	
3899 	console.log(changed);
3900 	return changed;
3901 };

3903 GenericStar.Editor.Generics.Generic.prototype.isOnScreen = function(offset, view) {
3904 	var x = this.getP("x");
3905 	var y = this.getP("y");
3906 	var w = this.getP("width");
3907 	var h = this.getP("height");
3908 	
3909 	if (!x || !y || !w || !h) return true;
3910 	
3911 	var ptCenter = {x: offset.x + view.w/2, y: offset.y + view.h/2};
3912 	
3913 	var sqr = function(x) {return x*x;};
3914 	
3915 	var dt1 = Math.sqrt(sqr(view.w/2) + sqr(view.h/2));
3916 	var dt2 = Math.sqrt(sqr(w/2) + sqr(h/2));
3917 	var dist = Math.sqrt(sqr(ptCenter.x - x) + sqr(ptCenter.y - y));
3918 	
3919 	return dist <= (dt1+dt2);
3920 };

3922 GenericStar.Editor.Generics.Generic.prototype.contains = function(px, py) {
3923 	var x = this.getP("x");
3924 	var y = this.getP("y");
3925 	var w = this.getP("width");
3926 	var h = this.getP("height");
3927 	var r = this.getP("rotation");
3928 	
3929 	if (!x || !y || !w || !h) return false;
3930 	if (!r) r = 0;
3931 	r = -r * Math.PI / 180;
3932 	var hw = w/2;
3933 	var hh = h/2;
3934 	px = px - x;
3935 	py = y - py;
3936 	var px2 = px * Math.cos(r) - py * Math.sin(r);
3937 	var py2 = px * Math.sin(r) + py * Math.cos(r);
3938 	
3939 	return (px2 >= -hw && px2 <= hw && py2 >= -hh && py2 <= hh);
3940 };
